25|$|On April 30 Iraqi Army units {{took the}} high ground {{to the south of}} RAF Habbaniya. An Iraqi envoy was sent to demand that no movements, either ground or air, were to take place from the base. The British refused the demand and then {{themselves}} demanded <b>that</b> <b>the</b> <b>Iraqi</b> units leave the area at once. In addition, the British landed forces at Basra and the Iraqis demanded that these forces be removed.|$|E
